-- Chrysler's September U.S. Vehicle Sales Jump 61%, Exceeding 48% Estimate
-- B y   J a m i e   B u t t e r s
-- 2010-10-01T15:42:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/chrysler-s-september-u-s-vehicle-sales-jump-61-exceeding-48-estimate.html
Chrysler Group LLC said its U.S.
vehicle sales in September rose 61 percent. The average estimate
of analysts surveyed by Bloomberg was for an increase of 48
percent.  Chrysler estimates that the seasonally adjusted annual
selling rate was 11.9 million for the month, exceeding the 11.7
million average of nine analysts’ forecasts.  General Motors Co. reported an 11 percent increase in sales
for the month. The automaker’s sales were expected to gain 13
percent, the average of three analysts surveyed by Bloomberg.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jamie Butters at   jbutters@bloomberg.net  